# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js App Router project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Package
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` (v2.0.0) to project dependencies
- Used npm to install the package following the project's existing package manager setup

### 2. Modified Files

#### `src/app/layout.tsx`
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component in the root layout's `<body>` tag, alongside the existing `<Analytics />` component
- This follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router (v13.5+)

#### `package.json`
- Added dependency: `"@vercel/speed-insights": "^2.0.0"`

#### `package-lock.json`
- Updated lockfile to reflect the new dependency and its transitive dependencies

## Implementation Details

The implementation followed the official Vercel Speed Insights Quickstart guide for Next.js App Router:
- Fetched latest documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart
- Identified the project as Next.js App Router (v16.2.10)
- Followed the framework-specific installation instructions for Next.js App Router
- Added the `<SpeedInsights />` component to the root layout file (`src/app/layout.tsx`)
- Placed it inside the `<body>` tag as recommended by the documentation

## Verification

### Build Status
- TypeScript compilation: ✓ Passed
- The build process compiled successfully with no TypeScript errors related to our changes
- Note: Build failed during page data collection due to missing DATABASE_URL environment variable, which is a pre-existing project configuration issue unrelated to Speed Insights

### Linting
- ESLint: ✓ Passed with no errors

### Testing
- No test script exists in package.json, so no tests were run

## Next Steps

To fully activate Speed Insights tracking:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard for your project
3. After deployment and traffic generation, performance data will appear in the Vercel dashboard

The Speed Insights component will automatically inject the tracking script and begin collecting Core Web Vitals and other performance metrics once deployed to Vercel.
